title: ICE to Buy Interactive Data for $5.2 Billion
text:
Intercontinental Exchange agreed to buy Interactive Data Corp. from Silver Lake and Warburg Pincus for about $5.2 billion, ending the financial-data providerâ€™s bid to go public.
The Atlanta-based exchange operator, which bought the New York Stock Exchange in 2013, is paying $3.65 billion in cash and $1.55 billion in shares.
